- 'Most recent' refers to the test executions with the latest start times;
- 'Test executions' are specific instances of running a test plan;
- 'Release version' is the version number of the software being tested.

sql:
SELECT status, COUNT(execution_id) AS total_executions
FROM test_executions
GROUP BY status;

external_knowledge:
- "fallen leaves" refers to failed test executions;
- "garden" refers to the test environment;
- "harvest" refers to the release version.

- "Top 5" refers to the highest-ranked items based on a specific metric;
- "Average execution times" are calculated by averaging the durations of multiple executions of the same test method across different environments;
- "Environments" represent different conditions or settings under which the tests are executed.

- The `total_time` is the sum of the durations of all executions within a test suite;
- The `duration_ms` is the execution time of each test in milliseconds;
- The `suite_name` is the descriptive name of the test suite.

- " heavyweight champion" refers to the test suite with the highest relative total test execution time;
- "total test execution time" is the sum of the durations of all test executions in a suite;
- "average test execution time" is the mean duration of test executions across all suites.

- "blossomed with test executions" refers to environments that have had test executions;
- "general bloom time" refers to the overall average duration of all test executions;
- "take longer than" refers to the average duration of test executions in a specific environment being greater than the overall average duration.

- 'Bloomed as 'passed' or 'failed'' refers to the status of the test execution being either 'passed' or 'failed';
- 'Sprouted after the dawn of 2022' refers to the release date being after January 1, 2022;
- 'Took more than a blink of an eye (1 second) to unfurl' refers to the duration of the test execution being greater than 1000 milliseconds.

- 'Passed tests' refers to test executions that have a status of 'passed';
- 'Active test suites' refers to test suites where `is_active` is set to 1;
- 'Overall average' is the average duration of all passed test executions across all suites.

- "test suites" are collections of test cases designed to validate specific aspects of a software system;
- "average duration" refers to the mean time taken for all test executions within a suite;
- "alphabetical order" ensures the results are sorted by the suite names in ascending order.

- "Most time-consuming" refers to the test class with the highest average execution time;
- "Blossoming the longest on average" is a metaphor for having the highest average duration;
- "Thrive the most" means having the most test executions;
- "Specific test environment (environment ID 1)" is the environment with the maximum total execution time.

- A 'test plan' is a document that describes the scope, approach, resources, and schedule of intended test activities;
- 'Test execution' refers to the process of running a test case and recording the results;
- 'Failed test' indicates a test that did not meet the expected criteria and is marked as 'failed' in the status;
- 'Total duration' is the sum of the durations of all failed tests within a test plan.

- 'Failed' test executions are those that did not pass the test criteria;
- 'Duration_ms' is the time taken for each test execution in milliseconds;
- The average duration is calculated across all test executions.

- 'v1.2.3' refers to a specific release version of the software being tested;
- The average duration is calculated in seconds for better readability;
- 'Passed tests' are those that have successfully completed without errors.
